snippet.title: SBOE February 3, 2016 Regular Business Meeting (Part 2 of 2)
snippet.description: The Indiana State Board of Education approved 2014-15 school corporation accountability grades during its regular business meeting. The grades approved by the Board reflect changes enacted by the Indiana General Assembly and signed into law by Governor Mike Pence to ensure that no school or school corporation is penalized by lower ISTEP+ scores during the state’s transition to more rigorous college and career ready academic standards. (Part 2 of 2)
